comment:
* Describes a request to download files over cell-broadcast. Instances of this class should be
 * created by the app when requesting a download, and instances of this class will be passed back
 * to the app when the middleware updates the status of the download.

variables.name: CURRENT_VERSION
variables.comment: Version code used to keep token calculation consistent.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)
public String getFileServiceId()
methods.comment: * @return The ID of the file service to download from.

methods.name: public Uri getSourceUri()
methods.comment: * @return The source URI to download from

methods.name: public Uri getDestinationUri()
methods.comment: * @return The destination {@link Uri} of the downloaded file.

methods.name: public int getSubscriptionId()
methods.comment: * @return The subscription ID on which to perform MBMS operations.

methods.name: public Intent getIntentForApp()
methods.comment:
* For internal use -- returns the intent to send to the app after download completion or
     * failure.
     * @hide

methods.name: public byte[] toByteArray()
methods.comment:
* This method returns a byte array that may be persisted to disk and restored to a
     * {@link DownloadRequest}. The instance of {@link DownloadRequest} persisted by this method
     * may be recovered via {@link Builder#fromSerializedRequest(byte[])}.
     * @return A byte array of data to persist.

methods.name: public static int getMaxAppIntentSize()
methods.comment:
* Maximum permissible length for the app's destination path, when serialized via
     * {@link Uri#toString()}.

methods.name: public static int getMaxDestinationUriSize()
methods.comment:
* Maximum permissible length for the app's download-completion intent, when serialized via
     * {@link Intent#toUri(int)}.

methods.name: public String getHash()
methods.comment:
* Retrieves the hash string that should be used as the filename when storing a token for
     * this DownloadRequest.
     * @hide

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)
